news.title: House prices in UK rise 0.3% in August: Halifax
news.para: British house prices experienced a 0.3% increase in August, marking the third consecutive monthly rise and pushing them 2.2% higher than the previous year, according to Halifax. Despite some uncertainty in the wider economy, the housing market demonstrates resilience, supported by improving affordability and steady demand. The average property price reached a new record high of 299,331 pounds.

news.title: Philippines extends land leases to 99 years to attract foreign investors
news.para: President Marcos Jr. has signed a law allowing foreign investors to lease private land in the Philippines for up to 99 years, replacing the previous 50-year limit with a 25-year extension. This aims to attract more offshore funding for long-term commercial and industrial projects, addressing investor concerns about lease contract stability.

news.title: Delhi: All 152 DDA flats sold within an hour under 'Apna Ghar Aawas Yojana'
news.para: Delhi Development Authority's 'Apna Ghar Aawas Yojana' witnessed remarkable success as all 152 flats were booked within an hour, projecting a revenue of Rs 100 crores. Due to high public demand, DDA has extended the scheme until November 26, 2025, offering ready-to-move-in flats across various categories and locations.

news.title: Vedanta beats Adani Group with ₹17,000 crore bid to acquire Jaiprakash Associates
news.para: Vedanta Group has emerged as the winning bidder for the debt-ridden Jaiprakash Associates (JAL), surpassing Adani Group with a Rs 17,000 crore offer. This bid translates to a net present value of Rs 12,505 crore for JAL, which faced insolvency proceedings due to loan defaults. The acquisition marks a significant development in the resolution of JAL's financial distress.

news.title: CCI dismisses complaint against Emaar India over Marbella villa project
news.para: The Competition Commission of India (CCI) has dismissed a complaint against Emaar India Ltd. regarding its "Marbella" villa project in Gurugram. The complaint alleged abuse of dominance and anti-competitive practices due to the construction of builder floors, which the complainant claimed violated commitments of an exclusive villa community.

news.title: Aparna Unispace unveils one of Asia’s largest experiential destinations for home designing & building solutions
news.para: About 105,000 sq. ft of dedicated space offering everything for your home, from floors to faucets to façades, under one roof.

news.title: Malaika Arora sells apartment in Mumbai ₹5.30 crore
news.para: Malaika Arora has sold her apartment in Runwal Elegante, Andheri West, for ₹5.30 crore, registering the transaction in August 2025. Purchased in March 2018 for ₹3.26 crore, the property appreciated by 62%, yielding a gain of ₹2.04 crore.

news.title: Shriram Properties to jointly develop 6.5 acres land in North Bengaluru
news.para: Shriram Properties has entered into a joint development agreement for a 6.5-acre land parcel in North Bengaluru, planning a residential project with a saleable area of 0.6 million sq ft and a gross development value of ₹500 crore.

news.title: Bengaluru: Taxed but abandoned in Abhivrudhi Garden Layout
news.para: For years, civic confusion has left more than 70 homes fending for themselves. Frustrated residents submitted a memorandum at KR Puram Corporation office, urging officials to finally deliver essential services long denied

news.title: Karnataka cabinet clears 1% fire cess on new multi-storey buildings
news.para: The Karnataka cabinet has approved a 1% fire cess on new multi-story buildings in Bengaluru and across the state, a move aimed at bolstering the fire force department's efficiency. Real estate developers express concern that this levy will increase costs, potentially raising property prices and dampening demand in an already strained market.

news.title: Maharashtra clears ₹6,500 crore for hi-tech ‘New Nagpur’
news.para: The Maharashtra cabinet has approved the ₹6,500-crore 'New Nagpur' project, a hi-tech city featuring an International Business and Finance Centre in Hingna taluka. NMRDA will implement the project, aiming to create over 5 lakh jobs through knowledge-based industries and startups.

news.title: Bengaluru: 85% of flat owners cleared in e-khata drive, only 4,000 appeals filed
news.para: Bengaluru's Greater Bengaluru Authority (GBA) cleared 1.2 lakh e-khata applications from flat owners, finding their tax records and sale deeds in order. However, 20,000 flats were flagged for discrepancies, with only 4,000 owners appealing. While some residents are complying and paying revised amounts, others contest the charges, arguing they shouldn't be penalized for errors.

news.title: Valor Estate may also move NCLT to revise Lavasa offer
news.para: Valor Estate is likely to petition the NCLT to revise its resolution plan for Lavasa Corp, following Welspun-Ashdan consortium being permitted to modify their payment timeline. Valor's lawyers objected to Welspun's allegations seeking disqualification of their bid and claimed discriminatory treatment by the RP for denying their request to update the plan.

news.title: To decongest Bengaluru, government plans AI-driven township in Bidadi
news.para: The Karnataka government has announced plans for Greater Bengaluru Innovation and Tech City (GBIT) in Bidadi, envisioning India's first AI-powered township. This project aims to alleviate pressure on Bengaluru by creating a self-sustaining ecosystem with residential, commercial, and social spaces.

news.title: Noida authority to upload names of property defaulters online
news.para: Noida Authority is set to publish lists of defaulters on its website to enforce transparency and recover long-pending dues from industry, group housing, commercial, and institutional sectors. Recovery proceedings have been initiated against group housing projects with dues exceeding Rs 350 crore.

news.title: Odisha government to hand over work orders for 50,000 homes for poor on Sept 17
news.para: The Odisha government will issue work orders for 50,000 houses under the Antyodaya Gruha Yojana on September 17 to provide permanent housing for economically weaker sections. Launched earlier this year, the scheme complements the PMAY-G, with over 1 lakh beneficiaries already included and further PMAY-G distribution planned for November.

news.title: About 1,014 sq yards plot fetch ₹33.4 crore in Chandigarh
news.para: Chandigarh's real estate market is booming, as evidenced by a recent auction that generated ₹168.85 crore, significantly exceeding the reserve price of ₹75.29 crore. A residential plot in Sector 33 sold for ₹33.4 crore, more than double its reserve price.

news.title: Home sales in Toronto decline in August as recovery stalls
news.para: Greater Toronto Area home sales experienced a slight dip in August, marking the first decline in five months, accompanied by a marginal decrease in prices, according to the Toronto Regional Real Estate Board. Despite lower borrowing costs and selling prices over the past year, affordability remains a challenge for average-income households.

news.title: Jaiprakash Associates lenders to meet on Sept 5; challenge process among five bidders likely
news.para: Lenders of the debt-ridden Jaiprakash Associates Ltd (JAL) will convene on Friday to discuss the 'challenge process' among five bidders, including Adani Group and Dalmia Bharat, aiming to maximize asset value. This follows a decision to conduct further negotiations with resolution applicants. The minimum bid value is set at Rs 12,000 crore.

news.title: West Bengal cabinet approves policy to convert non-residential plots for real estate, housing purposes
news.para: The West Bengal cabinet has approved a policy allowing conversion of under-utilised non-residential plots for real estate and housing, potentially unlocking land across the state. The decision, applicable to plots under the Urban Development and Municipal Affairs Department, involves a government-determined fee.
